quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  5,96,"Lawful for you is what you catch from the sea and the sustenance it provides; wholesome, for you and for the seafarer. But you are forbidden the game of the land while you are on Pilgrimage. And fear God, before whom you shall be herded"
  5,97,"God has made the Ka‘bah, the Sacred House, a standing shrine for people; also the sacred month, and the sacrificial offerings with their ornaments, so that you may know God has knowledge of all that the heavens and the earth contain; that God has knowledge of all things"
  5,98,"Know that God is stern in retribution, and that God is forgiving and compassionate"
  5,99,The Apostle‘s duty is only to give warning. God knows all that you reveal and all that you conceal
  5,100,"Say: ‘Evil and good are not alike, even though the abundance of evil may tempt you. Fear God, you that are of good sense possessed, that you may thrive.‘"
  5,101,"Believers, do not ask questions about things which, if made known to you, would only pain you; but if you ask them when the Koran is being revealed, they shall be made plain to you. God will pardon you for this; God is forgiving and gracious"
  5,102,"People asked them before you, only to disbelieve them thereafter"
  5,103,"God demands neither a bahīrah, nor a sā‘ibah, nor a waşīlah, nor a ḥāmi.¹ The unbelievers invent falsehoods about God; and most of them are lacking in judgement"